			<h2 class="body-current-exhibit">About the gallery:</h2>

			<p class="body-copy light grey">Representing over forty contemporary artists and estates, David Lusk Gallery was founded in Memphis, Tennessee in 1995. The Gallery opened a second location in Nashville’s invigorating Wedgewood-Houston neighborhood in 2014. The Gallery represents innovative and diverse artists from across the country, working across a wide range of artistic practices&mdash;from painting and sculpture to photography and video. Artists represented have exhibited extensively in museums and galleries worldwide. Both locations, Nashville and Memphis, are home to a distinct and exciting program of group and solo exhibitions, as well as lectures, panel discussions, and other public events.</p>

